{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/spurious-spatial-correlations/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Jon's Website","language":"en-US","siteUrl":"https://jons.website"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"e374f381-0119-5209-9115-8079e16afa98","excerpt":"In grad school, I took a course called Spatial Analysis. In it, I learned how to analyze geospatial data and look for trends. For our term project, we were each…\n","html":"<p>In grad school, I took a course called Spatial Analysis. In it, I learned how to analyze geospatial data and look for trends. For our term project, we were each to take a spatial dataset relevant to our fields and apply our skills. I recalled Tyler Vigen’s <a href=\"http://www.tylervigen.com\">Spurious Correlations</a>, a website that draws correlations between (hopefully) unrelated data sets such as the divorce rate in Maine and margarine sales per capita. There is a wealth of freely available spatial data made available by government agencies and ESRI, so I thought it would be funny to try out similar techniques with these data sets for the state of Maine.</p>\n<p>These are my results.</p>\n<h2 id=\"eagles-and-k-cups\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#eagles-and-k-cups\" aria-label=\"eagles and k cups permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Eagles and K-Cups</h2>\n<p>With the exception of Washington County, eagles seem to make their homes in areas where household K-Cup ownership is at or higher than the national average.</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/65e89612bf013eaa6e17ef9115432d8d/ef916/EaglesAndKCups.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 129.7297297297297%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"EaglesAndKCups\" title=\"EaglesAndKCups\" src=\"/static/65e89612bf013eaa6e17ef9115432d8d/fcda8/EaglesAndKCups.png\" srcset=\"/static/65e89612bf013eaa6e17ef9115432d8d/12f09/EaglesAndKCups.png 148w,\n/static/65e89612bf013eaa6e17ef9115432d8d/e4a3f/EaglesAndKCups.png 295w,\n/static/65e89612bf013eaa6e17ef9115432d8d/fcda8/EaglesAndKCups.png 590w,\n/static/65e89612bf013eaa6e17ef9115432d8d/ef916/EaglesAndKCups.png 815w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<h2 id=\"schools-and-aquifers\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#schools-and-aquifers\" aria-label=\"schools and aquifers permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Schools and Aquifers</h2>\n<p>589 of Maine’s 795 schools are within 3 km of an aquifer. This means that if you are at a school, there is a 74% chance that you are within walking distance of a significant source of groundwater.</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/9c147009e74113a05d3da1a922391fd9/ef916/SchoolsAndAquifers.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 129.7297297297297%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"SchoolsAndAquifers\" title=\"SchoolsAndAquifers\" src=\"/static/9c147009e74113a05d3da1a922391fd9/fcda8/SchoolsAndAquifers.png\" srcset=\"/static/9c147009e74113a05d3da1a922391fd9/12f09/SchoolsAndAquifers.png 148w,\n/static/9c147009e74113a05d3da1a922391fd9/e4a3f/SchoolsAndAquifers.png 295w,\n/static/9c147009e74113a05d3da1a922391fd9/fcda8/SchoolsAndAquifers.png 590w,\n/static/9c147009e74113a05d3da1a922391fd9/ef916/SchoolsAndAquifers.png 815w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<h2 id=\"us-cellular-coverage-and-oil-spill-hotspots\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#us-cellular-coverage-and-oil-spill-hotspots\" aria-label=\"us cellular coverage and oil spill hotspots permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>U.S. Cellular Coverage and Oil Spill Hotspots</h2>\n<p>US Cellular offers great coverage in areas where hazardous oil spills occur the most.</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/355ad21c7a272a862beba74734da2958/ef916/OilSpillsAndUSCellularCoverage.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 129.7297297297297%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"OilSpillsAndUSCellularCoverage\" title=\"OilSpillsAndUSCellularCoverage\" src=\"/static/355ad21c7a272a862beba74734da2958/fcda8/OilSpillsAndUSCellularCoverage.png\" srcset=\"/static/355ad21c7a272a862beba74734da2958/12f09/OilSpillsAndUSCellularCoverage.png 148w,\n/static/355ad21c7a272a862beba74734da2958/e4a3f/OilSpillsAndUSCellularCoverage.png 295w,\n/static/355ad21c7a272a862beba74734da2958/fcda8/OilSpillsAndUSCellularCoverage.png 590w,\n/static/355ad21c7a272a862beba74734da2958/ef916/OilSpillsAndUSCellularCoverage.png 815w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<h2 id=\"cemeteries-and-broadband-coverage\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#cemeteries-and-broadband-coverage\" aria-label=\"cemeteries and broadband coverage permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Cemeteries and Broadband Coverage</h2>\n<p>3875 of Maine’s 3929 cemeteries are located exactly within broadband coverage areas (98.63%).</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/2f987a1b2366d8806200948347746128/ef916/CemeteriesAndBroadband.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 129.7297297297297%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"CemeteriesAndBroadband\" title=\"CemeteriesAndBroadband\" src=\"/static/2f987a1b2366d8806200948347746128/fcda8/CemeteriesAndBroadband.png\" srcset=\"/static/2f987a1b2366d8806200948347746128/12f09/CemeteriesAndBroadband.png 148w,\n/static/2f987a1b2366d8806200948347746128/e4a3f/CemeteriesAndBroadband.png 295w,\n/static/2f987a1b2366d8806200948347746128/fcda8/CemeteriesAndBroadband.png 590w,\n/static/2f987a1b2366d8806200948347746128/ef916/CemeteriesAndBroadband.png 815w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<h2 id=\"red-cross-facilities-and-bedrock-formation-eras\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#red-cross-facilities-and-bedrock-formation-eras\" aria-label=\"red cross facilities and bedrock formation eras permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Red Cross Facilities and Bedrock Formation Eras</h2>\n<p>In what I can only consider to be a deliberate move, Red Cross has built their facilities in Maine on top of bedrock formed before the Devonian era. This means that if you got into a time machine and went back to the period at which the bedrock was formed beneath any Red Cross facility, you would not find sharks, ferns, trees, insects, or land vertebrates.</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/d7e56ee7d80d91d4323cc827b3abe804/b4098/RedCrossAndBedrock.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 113.51351351351352%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"RedCrossAndBedrock\" title=\"RedCrossAndBedrock\" src=\"/static/d7e56ee7d80d91d4323cc827b3abe804/fcda8/RedCrossAndBedrock.png\" srcset=\"/static/d7e56ee7d80d91d4323cc827b3abe804/12f09/RedCrossAndBedrock.png 148w,\n/static/d7e56ee7d80d91d4323cc827b3abe804/e4a3f/RedCrossAndBedrock.png 295w,\n/static/d7e56ee7d80d91d4323cc827b3abe804/fcda8/RedCrossAndBedrock.png 590w,\n/static/d7e56ee7d80d91d4323cc827b3abe804/b4098/RedCrossAndBedrock.png 816w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<p><strong>Disclaimer:</strong></p>\n<p>These datasets are in no way scientifically rigorous.</p>\n<h2 id=\"sources\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#sources\" aria-label=\"sources permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Sources</h2>\n<ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n<li><a href=\"http://www.maine.gov/dep/gis/datamaps/\">Maine Department of Environmental Protection</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.maine.gov/megis/catalog/\">Maine Office of GIS</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://usm.maine.edu/gis/digital-atlas\">University of Southern Maine’s Digital Atlas</a></li>\n<li>ESRI Online Catalog</li>\n</ul>\n<!--\n                                __.--'~~~~~`--.\n             ..       __.    .-~               ~-.\n             ((\\     /   `}.~                     `.\n              \\\\\\  .{     }               /     \\   \\\n          (\\   \\\\~~       }              |       }   \\\n           \\`.-~ -@~     }  ,-,.         |       )    \\\n           (___     ) _}  (    :        |    / /      `._\n            `----._-~.     _\\ \\ |_       \\   / /-.__     `._\n                   ~~----~~  \\ \\| ~~--~~~(  + /     ~-._    ~-._\n                             /  /         \\  \\          ~--.,___~_-_.\n                          __/  /          _\\  )\n                        .<___.'         .<___/\n-->","fields":{"slug":"/blog/spurious-spatial-correlations/","readingTime":{"time":123000,"words":410}},"frontmatter":{"title":"Spurious (Spatial) Correlations","subtitle":"\"Science\"","coverPhoto":{"publicURL":"/static/0b730b90939d2ba9fb0857c1f490a116/preview.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/0b730b90939d2ba9fb0857c1f490a116/2163c/preview.png","srcSet":"/static/0b730b90939d2ba9fb0857c1f490a116/2ec64/preview.png 204w,\n/static/0b730b90939d2ba9fb0857c1f490a116/3dff1/preview.png 407w,\n/static/0b730b90939d2ba9fb0857c1f490a116/2163c/preview.png 814w","sizes":"(min-width: 814px) 814px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/0b730b90939d2ba9fb0857c1f490a116/dfc09/preview.avif 204w,\n/static/0b730b90939d2ba9fb0857c1f490a116/0d611/preview.avif 407w,\n/static/0b730b90939d2ba9fb0857c1f490a116/60b1a/preview.avif 814w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 814px) 814px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/static/0b730b90939d2ba9fb0857c1f490a116/a5ced/preview.webp 204w,\n/static/0b730b90939d2ba9fb0857c1f490a116/09353/preview.webp 407w,\n/static/0b730b90939d2ba9fb0857c1f490a116/49256/preview.webp 814w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 814px) 814px, 100vw"}]},"width":814,"height":407}}},"coverPhotoAlt":"A picture of Maine with spatial data overlaid","date":"2018-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","isoDate":"2018-04-13","readableDate":"April 13, 2018","dateModified":null,"description":"Are eagle habitats and K-Cup usage spatially related? The results may shock you.","keywords":"spurious spatial correlations gis data maine"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/spurious-spatial-correlations/","previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/randomizing-uicolor-with-swizzling/"},"frontmatter":{"template":"blog-post","title":"Randomizing UIColor with Method Swizzling","draft":null}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2780354278","3903778693"]}